==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hooky
<hw>Hook"y</hw> <pr>(h⟦oocr⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>hookey</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Cf. <er>Hook</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, 3.]</ety> <def>A word used only in the expression <xex>to play
hooky</xex>, to be truant, to run away; -- used mostly of youths absent
from school without a valid reason and without the knowledge of their
parents. Also (figuratively and jocosely), to be absent from duty for
frivolous reasons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>This talk about boys . . . playing ball, and
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>hooky</qex>,⟦rdquo⟧ and marbles, was all moonshine.</q>
<rj><qau>F. Hopkinson Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hool</ent>⟦br⟧
